    <briefdescription>
<para>An XML namespace. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Note that prefix == NULL is valid, it defines the default namespace within the subtree (until overridden).</para>
<para>xmlNsType is unified with xmlElementType.</para>
<para>Note that the XPath engine returns XPath namespace nodes as xmlNs cast to xmlNode. This is a terrible design decision that can easily cause type confusion errors. In this case, the <computeroutput>next</computeroutput> member points to the xmlNode element to which the namespace node belongs. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
